      "date": "2017-06-06 19:49:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIs this feature needed anymore, now that we have nodemap?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "86bc3b9b9d0cbccc3cc4366ff3558a985a6a06da",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 689,
        "name": "Jeremy Filizetti",
        "email": "jeremy.filizetti@gmail.com",
        "username": "jfilizetti"
      },
      "date": "2017-06-07 13:04:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think so.  Nodemap doesn't restrict connections at the LND level.  So a rouge or untrusted system can still establish connections they just won't be able to proceed (easily) to the layers above ptlrpc.\n\nIn addition a misbehaving client for people working across administrative boundaries will lose the ability to disconnect such a client.\n\nI have a version of this patch for 2.9 but 2.10+ will require some significant changes due to multi-rail.  Once all the multi-rail changes are solidified I can probably work on a patch for 2.11.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
